main event: An observer reported seeing two objects in the sky that appeared to fade in and out of visibility, which was later evaluated to likely be the moon affected by atmospheric conditions.
interesting points: The observer initially saw a small spot in the sky that grew in size before slowly disappearing,The second object appeared in the same way shortly after,the conclusion suggested it was an optical illusion of the moon fading due to clouds,Dr. Hynek agreed with the investigator's assessment,A weather balloon was launched in a nearby location at about the same time which may have contributed to the sighting.
witness description: 24-year-old male, office worker, reported seeing the phenomena with others who also noticed it
